        "responseBody": "={{ $json }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "webhook-response-no-articles",
      "name": "Respond No Articles",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [1180, 400]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## KB Article Embedding Generator v2\n\n**Purpose:** Generate vector embeddings for KB articles to enable semantic search.\n\n### Triggers:\n- **Webhook**: POST /webhook/confluence/reindex\n- **Manual**: Click \"Execute Workflow\"\n\n### How it works:\n1. Fetches articles from `confluence_kb` without embeddings\n2. Prepares text combining title, metadata, and content\n3. Calls OpenAI API to generate embeddings (text-embedding-3-small)\n4. Updates the article with the embedding vector\n\n### Configuration:\n- OpenAI API credential required\n- PostgreSQL credential (Supabase)\n- Processes up to 50 articles per run\n\n### Integration:\n- Called by Workflow 5 after KB updates\n- Webhook URL: /webhook/confluence/reindex\n\n### Notes:\n- Uses text-embedding-3-small (1536 dimensions)\n- Estimated cost: ~$0.00002 per article",
        "height": 480,
        "width": 340
      },
      "id": "sticky-note",
      "name": "Workflow Info",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
